  "prompt": "Which are the best augmented reality companies in India? Why?",
  "response": "Several companies in India have made significant strides in the field of augmented reality (AR). Here are some of the top AR companies in India and the reasons they stand out:\n\n1. **Whodat**:\n   - **Why**: Whodat has developed a robust AR platform that offers solutions for various industries, including real estate, retail, and automotive. Their technology allows for real-time interaction and visualization, making them a leader in the AR space.\n\n2. **Scanta**:\n   - **Why**: Scanta focuses on creating AR-based security solutions and interactive experiences. Their innovative approach to using AR for cybersecurity and their engaging applications for entertainment and education make them a notable player.\n\n3. **Imaginate**:\n   - **Why**: Imaginate provides immersive AR and VR solutions for enterprise clients. Their products, such as 'NuSpace', offer collaborative virtual environments that enhance remote teamwork, training, and product demonstrations.\n\n4. **SmartVizX**:\n   - **Why**: SmartVizX specializes in creating AR and VR solutions for architecture and real estate. Their platform, 'Trezi', helps architects and designers visualize projects in a virtual space, improving design accuracy and client presentations.\n\n5. **Tesseract**:\n   - **Why**: Tesseract designs high-quality AR hardware, including headsets and glasses, and software solutions. Their focus on creating seamless AR experiences with advanced hardware sets them apart in the Indian market.\n\n6. **Quytech**:\n   - **Why**: Quytech offers custom AR solutions for various sectors, including healthcare, retail, and education. Their expertise in developing tailored AR applications and games has earned them a strong reputation.\n\n7. **EduAR**:\n   - **Why**: EduAR specializes in educational AR solutions. They create interactive learning tools that enhance student engagement and comprehension through immersive experiences.\n\nThese companies are leading the way in India\u2019s AR industry due to their innovative solutions, focus on specific industry needs, and ability to create engaging and practical AR applications.",
